  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.13.2`\r\nOS & Version: [**Raspberry Pi OS (64-bit)**]\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nI'm building a private network using raspberry pi 4 B.\r\nI follwed documentation https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/fundamentals/private-network\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nproblem is when i started geth it used too many disk space.\r\n![image](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/assets/67548026/8bebfb9b-5da4-4fd1-ac16-2f317d363bb4)\r\nAs you see **./geth/chaindata** uses too much disk space.\r\nSo I investigated **./geth/chaindata** using `ls -alh` command.\r\n![image](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/assets/67548026/ab4bcd4d-fa48-4f1a-8cda-af7129196243)\r\nAs you see, actual file size is very small(less than 1MB). But the disk usage is high(141MB)\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\ncommands used to build the network is as below.\r\n```\r\n\r\n./geth --datadir data --networkid 12345 --nat extip:192.168.0.23 --unlock 0x0d3B7BF41ba67ab1675e31348E78AaE4B43dd26F --mine --miner.etherbase=0x0d3B7BF41ba67ab1675e31348E78AaE4B43dd26F\r\n\r\n./geth --datadir data --networkid 12345 --port 30303 --bootnodes enode://07d88d56af00ffcad18966218efef3e58a4745f9ab3b3f78b12f0a0f0340b46c2020033c33666ea3d9a0599b5ef9b36d3bf03c8d83305d8bad3cadf316fb82cf@192.168.0.23:30303\r\n\r\n```\r\n+  **When I used leveldb as db.engine disk usage become normal**\r\n\r\n",
